## 7. Development Architecture

The development architecture describes how the code is organized into packages and layers. The system follows a strict top-down layered architecture where each layer only depends on the layer directly below it.

### Layer Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TB
  subgraph UI_Layer["UI Layer - Jetpack Compose"]
    TS["TimerScreen"]
    HS["HomeScreen"]
    CS["ChallengesScreen"]
    AS["AnalyticsScreen"]
  end

  subgraph ViewModel_Layer["ViewModel Layer"]
    TVM["TimerViewModel"]
    HVM["HomeViewModel"]
    CVM["ChallengesViewModel"]
    AVM["AnalyticsViewModel"]
  end

  subgraph Repository_Layer["Repository Layer"]
    SR["SessionRepository"]
    UR["UserRepository"]
    CR["ChallengeRepository"]
    AR["AnalyticsRepository"]
  end

  subgraph Domain_Layer["Domain Layer"]
    FS["FocusSession"]
    U["User"]
    L["Level"]
    VH["VirtualHome"]
    CH["Challenge"]
    AUS["AppUsageStat"]
  end

  subgraph Data_Layer["Data Layer - Room"]
    DB["AppDatabase"]
    SDAO["SessionDAO"]
    UDAO["UserDAO"]
    CDAO["ChallengeDAO"]
    ADAO["AnalyticsDAO"]
  end

  subgraph External_Services["External Services"]
    USM["UsageStatsManager"]
    WM["WorkManager"]
  end

  UI_Layer --> ViewModel_Layer
  ViewModel_Layer --> Repository_Layer
  Repository_Layer --> Domain_Layer
  Repository_Layer --> Data_Layer
  Repository_Layer --> External_Services
```

